content:
Analyze Your Data

You are here: Salesforce Help > Docs > Analytics > Create a Custom Report in Accessibility Mode

Create a custom report using the custom report wizard.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Essentials to Developer Editions.
User permissions needed: Create and Customize Reports and Report Builder.

From the Reports tab, click Create New Custom Report. Select the type of data and click Next.

Choose the report format and customize:

* Row and Column Headers
* Summarize Data
* Build Custom Summary Formulas
* Choose Fields
* Order Columns
* Limit Report Results

The report wizard supports up to 10 filters. Click Run Report or Export Details to save the report as an Excel file or other format.

Customizing reports can require running them a few times until you're finished customizing and ready to save.
title: Creating Custom Reports in Salesforce
